  "suggestion": "[systems-theory+control-theory+cognitive-architecture+dynamical-systems] REFINEMENT — Mechanism Precedence Cascade with Veto Gates. The model now has 6+ parallel layers (polyvagal → free energy → domain priors → attractor → narrative → regulatory focus → dissonance) but no explicit arbitration when they conflict. Implement a strict precedence cascade: (1) polyvagal SHUTDOWN vetoes all higher needs — output is always withdrawal/freeze regardless of other layers; (2) dissonance magnitude > 0.7 suspends regulatory focus — the mind can't pursue promotion/prevention while resolving contradiction; (3) narrative identity threat overrides momentary need hierarchy — people sacrifice comfort to protect self-story. Each veto has a numeric threshold and passes a 'residue' signal downstream. Math: cascade as a fold over layers, each emitting (output, veto_signal, residue); downstream layers receive residue as a prior perturbation. Result: same mechanisms, but now they compose coherently rather than vote democratically. — Math: f_cascade(s) = fold(layers, s, (acc, layer) → layer.veto(acc) ? force_veto_output(acc) : layer.apply(acc + acc.residue)); [existential-psychology+social-cognition+evolutionary-psychology+cultural-psychology] IMPLEMENT NOW — Terror Management Theory as Mortality Salience Signal (Becker 1973 / Solomon et al. 1991). When the situation activates mortality awareness — keywords: death, aging, illness, legacy, meaningless, finite, terminal — a scalar mortality_salience ∈ [0,1] is computed from keyword density × stimulus personalRelevance. This signal reshapes need precision: esteem ×(1 + 2ms), fairness toward in-group ×(1 + 1.5ms), belonging ×(1 + ms), understanding −ms×0.5, pleasure −ms×0.7. Crucially, worldview-congruent behaviors become attractors: conformity depth +ms×2, assert depth −ms. This predicts: religion and nationalism under existential threat, legacy-seeking and heroism, prejudice amplification, creative achievement as symbolic immortality. Implementation is 15 lines: extract ms score from stimulus description string, inject as precision modifiers before the free energy solve, add 'existential-defense' to the behavior vocabulary. — Math: ms = tanh(keyword_hits × stimulus.personalRelevance); precision_need *= (1 + TMT_weight[need] × ms); [cognitive-psychology+topology+geometry+social-cognition+temporal-psychology] NOVEL — Construal Level Theory as Psychological Distance Geometry (Trope & Liberman 2010). Cross-pollination from topology: every situation occupies a point in a 4-dimensional distance space — temporal (how far in future?), spatial (how far away?), social (how similar to self?), hypothetical (how probable?). Distance norm D = √(d_t² + d_s² + d_social² + d_hyp²) determines construal level: high D → abstract, principle-driven processing (regulatory focus: promotion, narrative: ideal self); low D → concrete, constraint-driven (regulatory focus: prevention, narrative: actual self). The model extracts distance signals from context strings ('someday' vs 'tomorrow', 'stranger' vs 'friend', 'maybe' vs 'definitely') and uses D to interpolate the weight between abstract-value response and concrete-situational response. This unifies why people make different decisions for others vs. themselves, near vs. far futures, and why perspective-taking induces empathy. Math: response = (1−α)·concrete_response + α·abstract_response where α = sigmoid(D − 0.5). — Math: D = norm([temporal_dist, spatial_dist, social_dist, hypothetical_dist]); α = σ(D − 0.5); response = lerp(concrete, abstract, α)",
